    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Use the </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Sweep-Display</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> to read the exact motion-values for any X-axis values, for all motion-derivative (P V A J) </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Sweep-Display</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> is almost the same as the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Motion-Value-Evaluator" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Motion-Value Evaluator</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:middle;">
